# Advanced Git Commands

---

## View Commit History (Graph)

Displays commits in a graphical format.

```bash
git log --oneline --graph --all
```

---

## Show Differences Between Commits

```bash
git diff
```

Compare two commits:

```bash
git diff commit1 commit2
```

---

## View Specific Commit Details

```bash
git show <commit-hash>
```

Example:

```bash
git show a1b2c3d
```

---

## Undo Last Commit (Keep Changes)

```bash
git reset --soft HEAD~1
```

---

## Undo Last Commit (Unstage Changes)

```bash
git reset --mixed HEAD~1
```

---

## Undo Last Commit (Delete Changes)

```bash
git reset --hard HEAD~1
```

---

## Restore Deleted or Modified File

```bash
git restore filename
```

---

## Restore All Files

```bash
git restore .
```

---

## Revert a Commit

Creates a new commit that reverses a previous commit.

```bash
git revert <commit-hash>
```

---

## Stash Current Changes

```bash
git stash
```

---

## View Saved Stashes

```bash
git stash list
```

---

## Apply Stashed Changes

```bash
git stash apply
```

---

## Apply and Remove Stash

```bash
git stash pop
```

---

## Delete a Stash

```bash
git stash drop
```

---

## Delete All Stashes

```bash
git stash clear
```

---

## Rename Current Branch

```bash
git branch -m new-branch-name
```

---

## Delete Local Branch

```bash
git branch -d branch-name
```

Force delete:

```bash
git branch -D branch-name
```

---

## Delete Remote Branch

```bash
git push origin --delete branch-name
```

---

## Fetch All Branches

```bash
git fetch --all
```

---

## Fetch and Remove Deleted Branches

```bash
git fetch --all --prune
```

---

## Add Upstream Repository

```bash
git remote add upstream <repository-url>
```

---

## Fetch from Upstream

```bash
git fetch upstream
```

---

## Merge Upstream Branch

```bash
git merge upstream/main
```

---

## Pull from Upstream

```bash
git pull upstream main
```

---

## Cherry-Pick a Commit

Copy a commit from another branch.

```bash
git cherry-pick <commit-hash>
```

---

## Rebase Current Branch

```bash
git rebase main
```

---

## Continue Rebase

```bash
git rebase --continue
```

---

## Abort Rebase

```bash
git rebase --abort
```

---

## Create a Tag

```bash
git tag v1.0
```

---

## List Tags

```bash
git tag
```

---

## Push Tags

```bash
git push origin --tags
```

---

## Remove a Tag

```bash
git tag -d v1.0
```

---

## Find Lost Commits

```bash
git reflog
```

---

## Clean Untracked Files

```bash
git clean -f
```

Delete untracked directories too:

```bash
git clean -fd
```

---

## View Current Branch

```bash
git branch --show-current
```

---

## View Remote Information

```bash
git remote -v
```

---

## Force Push

```bash
git push --force
```

Safer version:

```bash
git push --force-with-lease
```

---

## Git Help

```bash
git help
```

or

```bash
git <command> --help
```

Example:

```bash
git merge --help
```
